net.bytebuddy.implementation

Interface FieldAccessor.FieldLocator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FieldAccessor.FieldLocator.ForGivenType, FieldAccessor.FieldLocator.ForInstrumentedTypeHierarchy
    Enclosing class:
    FieldAccessor

    public static interface FieldAccessor.FieldLocator
    A field locator allows to determine a field name for a given method.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  FieldAccessor.FieldLocator.Factory
      A factory for creating a FieldAccessor.FieldLocator.
      static class  FieldAccessor.FieldLocator.ForGivenType
      A field locator that only looks up fields that are defined for a given type.
      static class  FieldAccessor.FieldLocator.ForInstrumentedType
      A factory that only looks up fields in the instrumented type.
      static class  FieldAccessor.FieldLocator.ForInstrumentedTypeHierarchy
      A field locator that finds a type by traversing the type hierarchy beginning with fields defined in the most specific subclass traversing the class hierarchy down to the least specific type.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      FieldDescription locate(String name, boolean staticMethod)
      Locates a field of a given name or throws an exception if no field with such a name exists.

    • Method Detail

      • locate

        FieldDescription locate(String name,
                        boolean staticMethod)
        Locates a field of a given name or throws an exception if no field with such a name exists.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the field to locate.
        staticMethod - true if the intercepted method is static.
        Returns:
        A representation of this field.
